{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":16513,"record_hash":"sha256:88930ec22a8d49812329fcb5ffd0fe85170321bd3301258cb4fe57f02d599ec0","timestamp":"2026-05-09T18:58:15.776Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"user","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"- **[P1] `--target` is parsed but never repo-normalized.** [cli.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:53) parses `Target`, then [gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:40) opens GitMeta and [uses it directly](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:41). A partial commit target like `commit:abc123` will be written under the partial value instead of resolving against the repo. POC fix: after `gix::discover` in [cli.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:55), resolve the target once against that repo and pass the resolved `Target` down.\\n\\n- **[P2] Agentlog dispatch is split across two CLI paths.** The real `but agentlog capture` path exits early in [lib.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but/src/lib.rs:150), but `match_subcommand` also handles it in [lib.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but/src/lib.rs:226), and the main command match still needs an `unreachable!` arm in [lib.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but/src/lib.rs:1471). That makes the trace noisier than the behavior. POC fix: keep hidden pre-settings commands in one routing point so `match_subcommand` only receives normal commands.\\n\\n- **[P2] Trace log creation can happen before agentlog validation.** `but` initializes tracing in [lib.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but/src/lib.rs:136) before the agentlog early return, and `trace::init` truncates/creates the log file via `File::create` in [trace.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but/src/trace.rs:44). The cheap agent/path validation is later in [cli.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:48). So `but -t --log-file X agentlog capture --agent cursor ...` can mutate `X` before failing validation. POC fix: either make clap reject invalid agents before `run`, or move the agentlog validation/dispatch ahead of trace file setup.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-09T18:58:15.776Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user","content":[{"type":"input_text","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"- **[P1] `--target` is parsed but never repo-normalized.** [cli.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:53) parses `Target`, then [gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:40) opens GitMeta and [uses it directly](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:41). A partial commit target like `commit:abc123` will be written under the partial value instead of resolving against the repo. POC fix: after `gix::discover` in [cli.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:55), resolve the target once against that repo and pass the resolved `Target` down.\\n\\n- **[P2] Agentlog dispatch is split across two CLI paths.** The real `but agentlog capture` path exits early in [lib.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but/src/lib.rs:150), but `match_subcommand` also handles it in [lib.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but/src/lib.rs:226), and the main command match still needs an `unreachable!` arm in [lib.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but/src/lib.rs:1471). That makes the trace noisier than the behavior. POC fix: keep hidden pre-settings commands in one routing point so `match_subcommand` only receives normal commands.\\n\\n- **[P2] Trace log creation can happen before agentlog validation.** `but` initializes tracing in [lib.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but/src/lib.rs:136) before the agentlog early return, and `trace::init` truncates/creates the log file via `File::create` in [trace.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but/src/trace.rs:44). The cheap agent/path validation is later in [cli.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:48). So `but -t --log-file X agentlog capture --agent cursor ...` can mutate `X` before failing validation. POC fix: either make clap reject invalid agents before `run`, or move the agentlog validation/dispatch ahead of trace file setup.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>"}]}}}